Reason for Change.value: Observed excessive foaming during batch VOY756 leading to material loss and extended processing time

mitigation strategies.value: Memo added to Annual Product Review

Reason for Change.value: The mixing sequence for Aryl Piperazine HCl and Sodium Acetate was revised to introduce Sodium Acetate first, followed by gradual addition of Aryl Piperazine under controlled RPM. This adjustment minimizes foaming and improves homogeneity. SOP-MFG-104 updated to reflect new sequence and RPM parameters.

Root Cause.value: Improper mixing order leading to excessive foaming and material loss

Description.value: During the compounding stage of batch VOY756, an unexpected increase in foam volume was observed after the addition of Aryl Piperazine HCl. The foam overflowed the mixing vessel, resulting in a material loss of approximately 0.3 kg and a 45-minute delay in processing. No contamination occurred, and the batch was contained.

Retrain all operators on revised SOP version

Add mixing order prompt to equipment HMI panel
